snippet: Sunday’s victory over Dallas seemed more like a consolation prize than the start of a championship run.
abstract: Jere Longman On Pro Football column holds that New York Giants victory over Dallas Cowboys to clinch NFC East title seems more like a consolation prize than the start of a championship run; observes that 9-7 Giants are first team to win its division with fewer than 10 victories since the NFL went to a 16-game schedule in 1978.
lead_paragraph: Sunday’s victory over Dallas seemed more like a consolation prize than the start of a championship run.

headline.seo: Giants Keep Resilience Amid Arid Stretch
headline.main: For Giants, Resilience if Not Excellence
headline.print_headline: For Giants, Resilience If Not Excellence
